# DevContainer Environment Variables Example
# 
# This file serves as a template for .devcontainer/.env
# Copy this file to .devcontainer/.env for local development

# GitHub Personal Access Token (required)
# Get your token from: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# Required permissions: repo, read:user, workflow
# GH_TOKEN=your_github_token_here

# Optional CLI Authentication (encode existing files with base64 -w 0)
# CODEX_AUTH=base64_encoded_content_of_codex_auth_json
# CLAUDE_AUTH=base64_encoded_content_of_claude_credentials_json

# Note for GitHub Codespaces users:
# - Tokens are provided through Codespaces secrets automatically
# - This empty .env file is still required for DevContainer runArgs
# 
# IMPORTANT: The actual .env file is in .gitignore to prevent token exposure